dct_title_s: A new and accurate map of the Seven United Provinces : compiled from the most approv'd maps & charts and adjusted by astronoml. observations
dct_description_sm: Relief shown pictorially and by shading for low lying areas. Cartouche title. From: A complete system of geography / by Emanuel Bowen. London : Printed for W. Innys, R. Ware, etc., 1747. Area: United Provinces or Netherlands north of the Rhine. Shows boundaries, marshes, banks, rivers and canals, roads, woodland and principal cities and towns. Prime meridian: London. Picture surrounding title cartouche shows a woman and man in traditional dress standing next to 9 round cheeses, near a house and a tree; in the background a single horse stands near a gate and past the gate two men, one on horseback, one on foot are following three dogs in pursuit of a stag.
dct_publisher_sm: [London : Printed for W. Innys, R. Ware, etc. 1747]
